55→/// Redirect stdout to a pipe, run a closure, capture its printed output.
56→///
57→/// A reader thread drains the pipe concurrently to prevent deadlock when
58→/// handler output exceeds the OS pipe buffer (~64KB on macOS).
59→///
60→/// # Safety
61→/// Uses dup/dup2/pipe to redirect fd 1 at the OS level. Safe because:
62→/// - MCP server is single-threaded per session (one tool call at a time)
63→/// - saved fd is always restored, even if the handler panics would unwind
64→///   (though handlers return i32, they don't panic in practice)
65→/// - pipe fds and saved fd are closed on all paths

